Real a = 10

Real b ~ LogNormal(logMean=0.0, logSd=1.0) observed as a
Real c ~ LogNormal(logMean=0.0, logSd=1.0) observed between [a + b, 100]

Real d[i] ~ LogNormal(logMean=i, logSd=1.0) observed as i for i in 1:10

// EXPECT AST
// (AS Real a 10)
// (OA (DR Real b (CA LogNormal (AA logMean 0.0) (AA logSd 1.0))) a)
// (OB (DR Real c (CA LogNormal (AA logMean 0.0) (AA logSd 1.0))) (+ a b) 100)
// (IS (OA (DR Real d (CA LogNormal (AA logMean i) (AA logSd 1.0))) i) i (R 1 10))
// EXPECT AST